Generated the Label developer guide document at `output/label.md`. The document covers:

- **Creating a Label**: Basic construction with `Label::New()`
- **Text Content and Styling**: Text, color, font configuration (family, size, weight, width, slant), and font variations
- **Text Alignment and Layout**: Horizontal/vertical alignment, line height control, and layout direction
- **Multi-line Text and Wrapping**: Multi-line mode, line wrap modes (WORD, CHARACTER, HYPHENATION, MIXED), and overflow handling
- **Font Size Scaling**: Font size scale with min/max constraints, system font size scale integration, and text fit feature
- **Marquee Animation**: Trigger policies, orientation, speed, loop count, delay, gap, and stop modes
- **Asynchronous Rendering**: Async rendering, signals for render/size computation completion, and render scale
- **Advanced Text Effects**: Text background color, cutout effect, mask effect, markup support, anchor links, and text styles (underline, shadow, outline, line-through, bevel)

All API examples are grounded in the public header `repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/public-api/label.h` and verified against sample code in `repos/dali-ui/samples/text/`.
